[thinking] I’m thinking about providing system.mapLibraryName as libbc-probe.so on Linux. It seems the tests will likely focus on Linux. The active call paths are only for Linux x86_64, and if I run it on a non-Linux/ARM system, loadDriver returns immediately. CI is probably set up for Linux x64. To ensure it's version and OS agnostic, I'm considering how to determine the actual OS from the dynamic class path. Should I force the os.name/os.arch system properties?
[thinking] 
