[assistant] Fixed the cause of the failures.
[assistant] 
[assistant] Root cause:
[assistant] - The fake `src/test/resources/native/linux/x86_64/probe/libbc-probe.so` resource was visible to the normal test classpath.
[assistant] - That made unrelated tests think native support existed, so Bouncy Castle tried `System.load(...)` on the placeholder text file and failed with `file too short`.
[assistant] 
[assistant] What I changed:
[assistant] - Removed the physical fake native resources under `src/test/resources/native/...`.
[assistant] - Updated `NativeLoaderTest` so the fake probe/deps resources are only provided by its isolated classloader.
[assistant] - Broadened the isolated classloader to load `org.bouncycastle.*` classes child-first, avoiding the `LinkageError` caused by mixing isolated FIPS classes with app-loader Bouncy Castle classes.
[assistant] - Avoided casting isolated Bouncy Castle objects back to app-loader interfaces.
[assistant] 
[assistant] This keeps the resource-access call sites reachable in `NativeLoader` without polluting the global test classpath or causing real native loading attempts in other tests.
[assistant] 
