\\nI’m pondering why `git diff` isn’t showing any output, and I think that the issue could be related to untracked files. So, I'll need to check if those files are being picked up properly. It seems like I might be looking at the wrong details, so I should also consider mentioning any removed fake resources to clarify the situation. Let's finalize this understanding correctly to avoid confusion!\"}]}"}, {"type": "text", "text": "Fixed the cause of the failures.\n\nRoot cause:\n- The fake `src/test/resources/native/linux/x86_64/probe/libbc-probe.so` resource was visible to the normal test classpath.\n- That made unrelated tests think native support existed, so Bouncy Castle tried `System.load(...)` on the placeholder text file and failed with `file too short`.\n\nWhat I changed:\n- Removed the physical fake native resources under `src/test/resources/native/...`.\n- Updated `NativeLoaderTest` so the fake probe/deps resources are only provided by its isolated classloader.\n- Broadened the isolated classloader to load `org.bouncycastle.*` classes child-first, avoiding the `LinkageError` caused by mixing isolated FIPS classes with app-loader Bouncy Castle classes.\n- Avoided casting isolated Bouncy Castle objects back to app-loader interfaces.\n\nThis keeps the resource-access call sites reachable in `NativeLoader` without polluting the global test classpath or causing real native loading attempts in other tests.\n\nPer instruction, I did not run the Gradle test command locally.", "textSignature": "{\"v\":1,\"id\":\"msg_0426bda6d0b044020169f9f336e740819ea9d6749f7f7e2250\",\"phase\":\"final_answer\"}"}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 251, "output": 271, "cacheRead": 53248, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 53770, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "stop", "timestamp": 1777988402029, "responseId": "resp_0426bda6d0b044020169f9f332c6b8819e99b1a91b9260b270"}}
