[thinking] **Considering system properties for tests**
[thinking] 
[thinking] I’m thinking about setting a system property in the static initializer of Bc_fipsTest. It could serve as a better central utility since static initializers only run when the class is loaded, but that doesn’t guarantee it'll happen before BC initialization. I wonder if I should create a junit-platform.properties file or configure the system property in build.gradle. It seems we can set a default system property for all tests in Gradle, especially focusing on the BC-FIPS context. What about native test configurations?
