[assistant] Implemented another refinement focused on making the `NativeLoader` call sites reachable during both JVM agent execution and Native Image test execution.
[assistant] 
[assistant] Key change:
[assistant] - Updated `tests/src/org.bouncycastle/bc-fips/2.1.2/build.gradle` to force the native loader path for all bc-fips tests:
[assistant]   - `org.bouncycastle.native.cpu_variant=missing-test-variant`
[assistant]   - `os.arch=amd64`
[assistant]   - `os.name=Linux`
[assistant]   - Applied to both JVM `Test` tasks and Native Image test runtime args.
[assistant] 
[assistant] Why this should help:
[assistant] - `FipsStatus.isReady()` triggers `NativeLoader.loadDriver()`.
[assistant] - Forcing Linux/amd64 makes `NativeLoader` probe `/native/linux/x86_64/probe/libbc-probe.so`.
[assistant] - Forcing a non-existent variant avoids loading a real variant library but still proceeds far enough to call:
[assistant]   - `NativeLoader.loadDriver()` resource probe
[assistant]   - `NativeLoader.getFile()` via dependency-list lookup
[assistant] - The missing variant then fails gracefully inside Bouncy Castle’s native loader without requiring a real native library load.
[assistant] 
[assistant] Also simplified `NativeLoaderTest.java` to use public Bouncy Castle APIs only:
[assistant] - `FipsStatus.isReady()`
[assistant] - `FipsNative.getServices()`
[assistant] - `NativeServices.getVariant()`
[assistant] - `NativeServices.isEnabled()`
[assistant] 
[assistant] No reachability metadata or native-image config files were added or modified.
[assistant] 
[assistant] Per instruction, I did not run the Gradle test command locally.
